==English==
===Etymology===
Representing a coloquial pronunciation of Arabic [[دوار|دَوَّار]].

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'du:ɑ:/

===Noun===
'''duar'''
# a [[camp]] or [[village]] of tents in an Arabic country
#:*'''1882''': The '''''duar''''' is in general made up of ten, fifteen, or twenty families, who are related to each other, and each family has a tent. — Edmondo de Amicis, ''Morocco: Its People & Places''

